{"id":"1092","name":"When To Leave","tagline":"Sets a reminder of when to leave, accounting for mode of travel and support for rich notifications.","icon":"ios12 c4274264319 g59757","latest":"8894","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>This shortcut will look at your calendar and ask you to choose an event with an address. That’s all you have to do! The shortcut will give you a reminder 10 minutes before you have to leave, and set an alarm for the time you actually need to head out. </p>\n<p>For rich notification support, use my other shortcut <a href=\"https://routinehub.co/shortcut/971\">Calendar Event ETA</a>. When the reminder comes up, just let it hang out until it’s time to go. When you leave, force-touch/tap-and-hold the notification to bring up the URL that will launch your directions and start your playlist. </p>\n<p><img alt=\"Badges\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/3QMzlEV.jpg\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"Made by\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/pi013nc.jpg\"></p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.4.1 - June 14, 2019, 12:36 p.m.</strong></p><p>Updated to work better with “Calendar Event ETA.”</p>"}